“Building high-performance and secure backend systems for healthcare applications.”

✅ Project Overview

This project follows REST API best practices and provides a foundation for a complete healthcare backend system.

The key features include:

✅	Business Feature
✅ User & Admin Authentication & Authorization (JWT, Spring Security)
✅ Patient Management (CRUD, Appointments)
✅ Pharmacy & Drugs Management
✅ Payment Management (Stripe & PayPal Integration)
✅ Employee & Staff Management
✅ Inventory Management
✅ Telemedicine Management (Video/Consultation Endpoints)
✅ Reporting & Analytics Dashboard
✅ Email Notifications & Alerts

✅ Each check mark indicates that the endpoint has been implemented and tested successfully.

⚙️ Tech Stack
Layer	Technology
Backend Framework	Spring Boot
Database	MySQL
ORM	Spring Data JPA
Security	Spring Security (JWT Authentication)
Payments	Stripe & PayPal Integration
Containerization	Docker
Build Tool	Maven / Gradle
Testing	JUnit & Mockito
📘 API Endpoints Summary

Below is a high-level summary of the key endpoints designed for this backend system:

Category	Description	Example Endpoint
✅ Auth	Register, Login, Logout	/api/v1/auth/register
✅ Users	Manage user profiles & roles	/api/v1/users/{id}
✅ Patients	CRUD patients, appointments	/api/v1/patients/{id}
✅ Pharmacy	Drugs inventory & management	/api/v1/pharmacy/drugs
✅ Payments	Stripe & PayPal payments	/api/v1/payments/checkout
✅ Employees	Staff & role management	/api/v1/employees/{id}
✅ Inventory	Manage medical supplies	/api/v1/inventory
✅ Telemedicine	Video consultation & sessions	/api/v1/telemedicine/sessions
✅ Analytics	Dashboard metrics & reports	/api/v1/analytics
✅ Admin	Manage system & reports	/api/v1/admin/users
🐳 Running Locally (Docker Setup)
# Clone the repository
git clone https://github.com/asohyannick/healthCare
cd healthCare-backend

# Build and run using Docker
docker-compose up --build

